b'' b'' b"if i don't think my belief is right and everyone else's belief is wrong," b"then i don't have a belief. this is simply what belief means." b'' b'[more stuff deleted]' b'' b'this seems to be a pretty arogant definition of belief. my beliefs' b'are those things which i find to be true based on my experience of the' b'world. this experience includes study of things that i may not have' b'experienced directly. but even then, i can only understand the' b'studies to the extent to which i can relate what i study back to what' b'i have experienced.' b'' b'which means that by beliefs about god are directly related to my' b'experience of god. having experienced god, i try to make sense of' b'that experience. i study religion and read the bible. i find things' b'that echo what i have already experienced. out of this i build my' b"beliefs. i also find things that don't match my experience. that" b"doesn't make them false. they just don't match my experience. maybe" b"i will understand that stuff later. i don't know. maybe all of my" b'beliefs are wrong. i can change my beliefs.' b'' b'if someone else has beliefs that are different from mine, so what.' b'neither of us are necessarily wrong. someone else is making sense out' b'of a different set of experiences. even though we have different' b'explanations and beliefs, if we talk we might even discover that the' b'underlying experiences are similar.' b'' b'some people approach religion as a truth that can only exist in one' b'form, and usually has a single revelation. the more dogmatic and' b'inflexible the belief system, the more arrogant it will appear to an' b'outsider. there is another approach possible, however. god is a' b'mystery. i am trying to solve the mystery, so i look at the evidence' b'available to me. i try to arrive at the best understanding that i can' b'based on the evidence. new evidence may cause me to change my' b'understanding. when i encounter someone with a different belief than' b"my own, it isn't a threat, it is an opportunity to perhaps discover" b'something new about this mystery i can never fully comprehend.' b'' b'peace' b'will taber' b'----------------------------------------------------------------------------' b'| westboro, mass. change without notice. b'|---------------------------------------------------------------------------' b"| when all your dreams are laid to rest, you can get what's second best, b"|\tbut it's hard to get enough.\t\tdavid wilcox b'----------------------------------------------------------------------------' 